The terrain sorter itself has no obvious internal count mismatch: `queue()` adds 9 vertices when it pushes one primitive, and `prepareToDraw()` emits 9 per primitive in the list. The caller, however, filters terrain primitives by visibility/backface before queueing, which explains NPC-near world-space terrain batches but not a tail-only stale transform unless the D3D11 upload/draw count is using stale lock capacity rather than the filled lock count.
