**#1 match: `ClientTerrainSorter::PrimitiveNode`**

[ClientTerrainSorter.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/appearance/ClientTerrainSorter.cpp:69) builds the exact 36-byte format:

`position(12) + normal(12) + color0(4) + 1 * tc2(8) = 36`

Lock/write site: [ClientTerrainSorter.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/appearance/ClientTerrainSorter.cpp:296)

Per-vertex write loop: [ClientTerrainSorter.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/appearance/ClientTerrainSorter.cpp:311)

Key match:

```cpp
vertexBuffer.lock(numberOfVertices);

for each primitive:
  for (int j = 0; j < 9; ++j)
    vi.setPosition(positionList[j]);
    vi.setNormal(normalList[j]);
    vi.setColor0(colorList[j]);
    vi.setTextureCoordinates(0, ...);
```

Why this is the best match:

- `1647 = 183 * 9`
- `2664 = 296 * 9`
- the tail size `~27` is exactly `3 * 9` vertices
- format is exactly 36 bytes when `primitive->getNumberOfTextureCoordinateSets() == 1`
- it writes large dynamic batches, not 4-vertex billboards
- it writes terrain primitive positions near the camera/player/NPC area, then binds with terrain transform at [ClientTerrainSorter.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/appearance/ClientTerrainSorter.cpp:366)

Exact tail mechanism for this candidate:

`ClientTerrainSorter::queue()` counts one terrain primitive as 9 vertices at [ClientTerrainSorter.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/appearance/ClientTerrainSorter.cpp:576). If the D3D11 lock/bind path or cached `PrimitiveNode` state presents a lock count three primitives larger than the actual primitives written, the final 27 vertex slots are never overwritten and retain prior skin-ring contents. The source-side unit is 9 vertices, so a contiguous stale tail of ~27 points directly at “three terrain primitives worth of stale/unwritten tail,” not skeletal mesh triangles.

**Other 36-byte dynamic writers checked**

1. `ClientDynamicRadialFloraManager::FloraRenderBucket::LocalShaderPrimitive`  
   Format: [ClientDynamicRadialFloraManager.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/flora/ClientDynamicRadialFloraManager.cpp:191)  
   Lock/write: [ClientDynamicRadialFloraManager.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/flora/ClientDynamicRadialFloraManager.cpp:552)  
   Writes world-space quads directly by raw struct copy. But counts are `radialNodeCount * 4`, so `1647` cannot match. Exclude.

2. `NebulaShellShaderPrimitive`  
   Format: [NebulaShellShaderPrimitive.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/space/NebulaShellShaderPrimitive.cpp:88)  
   Lock/write: [NebulaShellShaderPrimitive.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/space/NebulaShellShaderPrimitive.cpp:334)  
   Writes world-space quad corners, but counts are `quadCount * 4` and this is space/nebula rendering, not NPC-ground rendering. Exclude.

3. `SpriteAppearance`  
   Format: [SpriteAppearance.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientObject/src/shared/appearance/SpriteAppearance.cpp:103)  
   Lock/write: [SpriteAppearance.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientObject/src/shared/appearance/SpriteAppearance.cpp:208)  
