Bottom line: the fingerprint points at `ClientTerrainSorter::PrimitiveNode`, not skeletal animation. The `1647/2664` counts and `~27` stale tail are the giveaway: terrain sorter batches in 9-vertex terrain primitives, and 27 vertices is exactly three stale/missing terrain primitives at the end of the dynamic VB slice.
